  WHAT THIS FILE DOES
  ───────────────────
  A sitemap tells Google and Bing exactly which pages exist on your site and
  when they were last updated. Without one, crawlers may miss pages or
  re-crawl them less frequently.

  HOW TO SUBMIT THIS SITEMAP
  ──────────────────────────
  1. Go to https://search.google.com/search-console
  2. Add your property: https://japhet996sunday-cell.github.io/build-apps-blog/
  3. Navigate to Sitemaps (left sidebar)
  4. Enter: sitemap.xml  →  Submit

  HOW TO MAINTAIN THIS FILE
  ──────────────────────────
  Every time you publish a new post:
    1. Create the HTML file in /posts/
    2. Add the post object to posts.json
    3. Copy one of the <url> blocks below and update:
         <loc>      → full URL of the new post (https://...github.io/.../posts/slug.html)
         <lastmod>  → use updatedDate if it exists, otherwise publishDate (YYYY-MM-DD)
    4. Uncomment the block if it was previously commented-out (scheduled)

  FIELD REFERENCE
  ───────────────
  <loc>        Required. The full, absolute URL of the page.
  <lastmod>    The date the page content was last meaningfully changed (YYYY-MM-DD).
               Use updatedDate from posts.json when available, else publishDate.
  <changefreq> Hint to crawlers: how often this page is likely to change.
               homepage = "weekly" | blog posts = "monthly"
  <priority>   Relative importance: 1.0 (highest) to 0.1 (lowest).
               This is a hint, not a ranking signal.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
